HEADWORD: Dentine
<hw>Den"tine</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>dentine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The dense calcified
substance of which teeth are largely composed. It contains less animal
matter than bone, and in the teeth of man is situated beneath the
enamel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dentiphone</ent>⟦br⟧
